title: Wrong data set result returned when setting an invalid filter expression on row[0]
description: Currently, when attempting to set a filter using an expression like 'row[0] equals to 0', the result set is not returned correctly. Instead, it either returns null or an unexpected result set.
OB: The result set is not returned correctly when setting an invalid filter expression on row[0].
EB: A relevant error message should be displayed when attempting to set an invalid filter expression on row[0].
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Set a filter using an expression like 'row[0] equals to 0'.
2. Verify the result set is not returned correctly.
3. Check for any relevant error message displayed.
